quran[10]{c,v,t}:
  17,18,"Whoever is willing (to gain) (this) hasty (world), We (quickly) hasten for him therein whatever We decide to whomever We will; thereafter We make for him Hell where he will roast, reprobated and (regretfully) rejected"
  17,19,"And whoever is willing (to gain) the Hereafter and diligently endeavors after it as he should (endeavor), being a believer, then those, their endeavor is to be thanked"
  17,20,"Each do We supply, these and these (too) from your Lord?s gift, and in no way can your Lord's gift be walled up"
  17,21,"Look how We have graced some of them over the others, (Literally: over some \"others\") and indeed the Hereafter is greater in degrees and greater with marked graciousness"
  17,22,"Do not make up with Allah another god, for then you will sit reprobated (and) abandoned"
  17,23,"And your Lord has decreed that you should not worship any except Him (only) and (to show) fairest companionship to parents; in case ever one or both of them reaches old age (Literally: being great \"in years\") in your presence, do not say to them, \"Fie!\" nor scold them; and speak to them respectful words (Literally: say to them an honorable saying)"
  17,24,"And lower to them the wing of humbleness out of mercy and say, \"Lord! Have mercy on them, as they reared me (when I was) small"
  17,25,"Your Lord knows best whatever is in your selves. In case you are righteous, then surely He has been Ever-Forgiving to the constant resorters (to Him)"
  17,26,"And bring to a near kinsman his true (right) and (to) the indigent and the wayfarer; and do not squander wantonly (Literally: in \"wanton\" squandering)"
  17,27,"Surely the squanderers have been brethren of Ash-Shayatin (The all-vicious ones, i.e., the devils), and Ash-Shaytan has ever been ever-disbelieving to his Lord"